-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Etisalat, Mobily, Aldrees Petroleum
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-02-12T13:04:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/persian-gulf-stocks-emirates-telecommunications-dp-world.html
Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  fell
0.4 percent to 2,456.22, the lowest this month, at the 2 p.m.
close in the emirate.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols follow company names.  Aldrees Petroleum & Transport Services Co.  (ALDREES AB)
advanced 0.9 percent to 46.40 riyals, the highest in a week. The
gasoline station operator in Saudi Arabia said it is seeking
shareholder approval to raise its capital 20 percent to 300
million riyals ($80 million) by offering one free share for
every five held.  Emirates Telecommunications Co. (ETISALAT)   dropped 2.1
percent, the most since Jan. 17, to 9.25 dirhams. The United
Arab Emirates’ largest telephone company said full-year profit
declined 23 percent after it booked an impairment of 1 billion
dirhams on its operations in  India .  Etihad Etisalat Co. (EEC)   gained 2.1 percent to 60
riyals, the highest since October 2007. Saudi Arabia’s second-
largest phone company known as Mobily signed a 10 billion-riyal
($2.7 billion) refinancing agreement with seven local banks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
